        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:44PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 543 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Gay, or near Yatesville Lake State Park, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Louisa, Wayne, Yatesville Lake State Park, Fort Gay, East Lynn Lake,
Fallsburg, East Lynn, Genoa, and Buchanan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
